# -*- mode: snippet -*-
# name: review fix
# key: revfix
# --

Read the code review findings from mds/code-review*.md file/s. Create an aggregate list of issues and remove duplicates.

- If a finding does not make sense or it makes wrong assumptions, ignore it.
- Fix each High or Medium importance finding and write tests before fixing it. Use tdd and red -> green technique.
- For the Low importance finding, if it is an easy refactor, fix it. Otherwise, if implies a large refactoring, ignore it.
- Print a summary of the fixes sorted by importance at the end.